# Cloudflare Pages / Workers static-assets redirects file
# https://developers.cloudflare.com/pages/configuration/redirects/
#
# NOTE: A rule forcing /404.html with a literal "404" status code used to
# live here. That syntax is only valid on classic Cloudflare Pages — this
# project deploys via `wrangler deploy` (the newer Workers static-assets
# model, confirmed by the deploy logs), whose _redirects parser only
# accepts 200/301/302/303/307/308 and hard-fails the whole deploy on any
# other code. 404 handling for that model is instead configured in
# wrangler.toml via `assets.not_found_handling: "404-page"`, which is the
# correct mechanism here — so no rule is needed in this file for that.
#
# Add real redirect rules below if you need them, using only the status
# codes listed above, e.g.:
#   /old-page   /new-page   301
